’t it strike you as rather monotonous and forced? You ought to dwell in some other clime with plenty of sunshine: sunshine is the friend of painters. I can see, though, that this topic doesn’t interest you. Let’s talk of something else. Tell me, for instance, how do matters stand with that allotment of yours?”

“Dashed if I know. They keep sending me letters in German; I’d ask you for a translation, but it bores me stiff.… And—well, I either lose the things or just tear them up a